      "note": "Open-source, dual-use, and server/edge deployments may evade controls; the proposal lacks scope for weights, data, APIs, model variants, and deployment contexts."
    },
    {
      "severity": 5,
      "type": "ambiguity",
      "note": "Definition of 'high-risk' is not specified; lacks criteria, thresholds, domain-specific considerations, and how risk evolves with new capabilities."
    },
    {
      "severity": 5,
      "type": "missing",
      "note": "Due process specifics (who adjudicates, how hearings, timeline, and appeal mechanisms) are not described."
    },
    {
      "severity": 5,
      "type": "logic",
      "note": "Assumes reliable real-time assessment of imminent severe harm; in practice, many harms are emergent or latent, risking overreach or delayed action."
    },
    {
      "severity": 4,
      "type": "factual",
      "note": "Feasibility and sufficiency of enforcement infrastructure (audits, reporting, certifications) depend on resources; small actors may be disproportionately burdened."
    },
    {
      "severity": 5,
      "type": "missing",
      "note": "International coordination risks: sovereignty, privacy, and security tensions; harmonization may be impractical and regulatory arbitrage may persist."
    },
    {
      "severity": 4,
      "type": "overconfidence",
      "note": "Claims that safeguards can be rights-respecting without dampening safety or innovation may be overly optimistic; trade-offs and long-term effects are uncertain."
    },
    {
      "severity": 5,
      "type": "missing",
      "note": "No plan for evaluation, metrics, or sunset/rollback mechanisms to measure effectiveness or correct course."
    },
    {
      "severity": 3,
      "type": "ambiguity",
      "note": "What constitutes 'proportionate penalties' is unclear; no guidance on scaling penalties with harm, breach severity, or enforcement discretion."
    }
  ]
}

